{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dc0fda07-c715-4c0a-aedf-ea10ac029682","content":"Here's how to skip tests with a reason in each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results rather than failing or passing, and the reason string appears in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ca17b648-eeaf-45a4-acd1-5e9b4765db91","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to look anything up.","outputTokens":229,"requestId":"BC2C:1554D2:258BF6:2BC91A:69FA93D1"},"id":"e1d13f30-0709-49de-8e38-c7607bdf89e5","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:05:27.594Z","parentId":"5369f771-ba61-4f6c-87b3-75ab9995f606"}
